The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for medical images. The use of Radon transformation and barcodes for tagging and annotating medical images falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach of finding optimal projections using an evolutionary algorithm involves machine learning and optimization techniques, which can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of the IRMA dataset, which contains medical images, suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
